libraries

library(lattice)
library(latticeExtra)

ref1

0.1 histogram

histogram(formula,
          data, 
          type = c("percent", "count", "density"),
          nint = if(is.factor(x)) length(levels(x))
          else round(log2(length(x))+1),
          endpoints = range(x[!na.x]),
          breaks = if(is.factor(x)) seq(0.5, length = length(levels(x))
                   + 1) else do.breaks(endpoints, nint),
          equal.widths = FALSE, 
          ...)

head(mtcars)
hist(mtcars$mpg)

lattice::histogram(~mpg,data=mtcars) # bin, y, colors differ

lattice::histogram(~mpg, data = mtcars, 
          # Specify number of bins
          nint = 15,
          # Specify quantity displayed on y-axis
          type = "count")

  • percent, the default, gives percentage or relative frequency.
  • count gives bin count, which is the default in hist().
  • density gives a density histogram.
histogram(~mpg|factor(cyl), data = mtcars,nint = 15, type = "count")

histogram(~mpg|factor(cyl), data = mtcars,nint = 15, type = "count",
          main="baslik",xlab="x",ylab="y")

densityplot(~ mpg, data=mtcars,main="Density Plot", 
   xlab="Miles per Gallon")

0.2 scatterplot

xyplot(mpg~wt,data=mtcars, 
   main="Scatterplots by Cylinders and Gears", 
   ylab="Miles per Gallon", xlab="Car Weight")

xyplot(mpg~wt|as.factor(cyl),data=mtcars, 
   main="Scatterplots by Cylinders and Gears", 
   ylab="Miles per Gallon", xlab="Car Weight")

xyplot(mpg~wt|as.factor(cyl)*as.factor(gear),data=mtcars, 
   main="Scatterplots by Cylinders and Gears", 
   ylab="Miles per Gallon", xlab="Car Weight")

splom(mtcars[c(1,3,4,5,6)], 
   main="MTCARS Data")

cloud(mpg~wt*drat,data=mtcars)

cloud(mpg~wt*drat|as.factor(cyl),data=mtcars)

0.3 dotplot

dotplot for each combination of two factors

dotplot(as.factor(cyl)~mpg|as.factor(gear), data=mtcars,
   main="Dotplot Plot by Number of Gears and Cylinders",
   xlab="Miles Per Gallon")
